{"questionId":"32989360","questionHtml":"<p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1000</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5000</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to eliminate the denominator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>6000</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>5000</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>6000</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5000</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5000</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept correct equivalent forms, eg. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>6000</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>5000</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5000</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to express <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> with a common denominator of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>600</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>500</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>600</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>500</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>500</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept correct equivalent forms.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1000</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5000</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32989360","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.1ci","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that Tn=10001.1n-1+5000.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSec